in basement level one
at the time of the collapse,

32
00:02:18,805 --> 00:02:20,431
so the actual death toll...

33
00:02:22,433 --> 00:02:23,601
My mom is

34
00:02:23,852 --> 00:02:26,688
under the collapsed department store.

35
00:02:26,771 --> 00:02:28,982
-I want my coffee.
-Yes, ma'am.

36
00:02:30,608 --> 00:02:32,402
Please save my mom's life.

37
00:02:35,155 --> 00:02:37,699
The rescue workers are doing their best.

38
00:02:37,782 --> 00:02:39,826
I told you to wait just a little longer.

39
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:41,578
Leave it up to them and eat.

40
00:02:41,661 --> 00:02:45,290
Yes, count on them
that they will rescue your mom

41
00:02:45,373 --> 00:02:46,666
and just eat your food.

42
00:02:46,749 --> 00:02:49,961
You haven't eaten anything
since yesterday. Come, now.

43
00:02:51,296 --> 00:02:53,590
So, are you enjoying your barbecue?

44
00:02:53,798 --> 00:02:55,383
Yes, I am.

45
00:02:55,466 --> 00:02:57,594
The housekeeper did a very good job.

46
00:02:57,802 --> 00:03:01,055
-Ma'am, can you fix a meal for Kang--
-How do you expect me to eat?

47
00:03:04,142 --> 00:03:05,393
My mom

48
00:03:05,977 --> 00:03:09,063
must be stuck in the dark,
without even a sip of water to drink.

49
00:03:10,106 --> 00:03:12,150
I keep thinking about that,

50
00:03:12,233 --> 00:03:14,277
and I just can't eat.

51
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:16,404
All right. Don't eat if you can't eat.

52
00:03:16,487 --> 00:03:17,864
Don't force yourself.

53
00:03:18,406 --> 00:03:22,785
Even if something about Su-hui comes up,
don't bother to prepare a funeral.

54
00:03:22,869 --> 00:03:25,330
If it becomes public,

55
00:03:25,413 --> 00:03:28,082
it will just be
something people would gossip about.

56
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:30,001
Okay, Mom.

57
00:03:31,169 --> 00:03:32,462
Jun, eat up.

58
00:03:40,929 --> 00:03:43,848
We'll need to collect
all of your mom's belongings

59
00:03:43,932 --> 00:03:45,558
and burn them.

60
00:03:45,934 --> 00:03:47,727
If we don't, her soul might not be able

61
00:03:47,810 --> 00:03:49,562
to move on or rest in peace

62
00:03:49,646 --> 00:03:51,814
and linger in this world as a ghost.

63
00:03:54,025 --> 00:03:57,153
She should've just continued
to live quietly in Wando.

64
00:03:57,737 --> 00:03:59,530
Why did she come to Seoul?

65
00:04:01,282 --> 00:04:02,408
Ma'am.

66
00:04:03,117 --> 00:04:04,118
What is it?

67
00:04:14,003 --> 00:04:16,547
Please burn these, too.

68
00:04:17,131 --> 00:04:19,342
What is it? Aren't those chocolates?

69
00:04:19,926 --> 00:04:23,096
You used to give up sleep
to have chocolate, boy.

70
00:04:23,221 --> 00:04:24,806
Why burn them and not eat them?

71
00:04:25,598 --> 00:04:27,141
I won't have chocolate

72
00:04:27,642 --> 00:04:29,102
ever again.

73
00:04:29,519 --> 00:04:30,353
Why not?

74
00:04:30,895 --> 00:04:32,188
If I eat them,

75
00:04:33,106 --> 00:04:34,107
I'll want to

76
00:04:35,316 --> 00:04:37,485
go back to Wando.

77
00:04:38,319 --> 00:04:40,363
What do you mean?

78
00:04:41,698 --> 00:04:43,116
I want real food.

79
00:04:44,158 --> 00:04:45,743
Please fix me a meal.

80
00:04:47,412 --> 00:04:50,456
Eat slowly.
No one's going to steal your food.

81
00:04:51,165 --> 00:04:53,084
You had nothing but water for three days.

82
00:04:53,167 --> 00:04:55,837
If you suddenly eat like that,
you'll get a tummy ache.

83
00:05:03,511 --> 00:05:06,723
After all, I think
I'm the one who's lost, Min-seong.

84
00:05:08,266 --> 00:05:10,476
I thought I was going the right way.

85
00:05:16,858 --> 00:05:19,610
EPISODE 9

86
00:05:24,032 --> 00:05:27,035
Will I be able to find my way again?

87
00:05:33,958 --> 00:05:37,337
First they gave me shit,
and now they show me love.

88
00:05:43,384 --> 00:05:44,218
Your hand.

89
00:05:55,063 --> 00:05:56,230
Is it this hand?

90
00:05:56,606 --> 00:05:58,524
The one that doesn't listen to you.

91
00:06:00,276 --> 00:06:01,110
Yes.

92
00:06:03,029 --> 00:06:03,988
Have a seat.

93
00:06:14,082 --> 00:06:15,208
How's the rehab going?

94
00:06:16,459 --> 00:06:17,293
I'm doing my best.

95
00:06:19,962 --> 00:06:22,340
Thanks to you saving that doctor's wife,

96
00:06:22,423 --> 00:06:24,801
the public has become
much more friendly towards us.

97
00:06:25,468 --> 00:06:27,303
The hospice

98
00:06:27,387 --> 00:06:29,597
has become a hotbed of horrible crime,

99
00:06:29,889 --> 00:06:31,849
so even those civic groups
and organizations

100
00:06:31,933 --> 00:06:35,686
that were against us shutting it down
will be quiet for a while.

101
00:06:36,270 --> 00:06:37,105
Well done.

102
00:06:38,147 --> 00:06:39,357
From now on,

103
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:42,985
We're going to get rid of
that useless hospice

104
00:06:43,069 --> 00:06:47,532
and replace it with the best exclusive
retirement community in this country

105
00:06:49,033 --> 00:06:50,701
I want you to be in charge of it.

106
00:06:53,371 --> 00:06:55,373
I can't trust the others.

107
00:06:56,874 --> 00:06:59,377
If you help me shut down the hospice

108
00:06:59,919 --> 00:07:02,713
and make my long-cherished ambition
come true,

109
00:07:02,797 --> 00:07:04,424
I will wholeheartedly trust you

110
00:07:04,924 --> 00:07:08,803
and even pass down
the Geosung Foundation to you.

111
00:07:10,388 --> 00:07:11,264
Okay?

112
00:07:17,395 --> 00:07:19,188
SON

113
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:24,026
He's driving me nuts.

114
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:25,778
He even turned his phone off.

115
00:07:25,862 --> 00:07:28,406
Where the hell is he?

116
00:07:28,489 --> 00:07:29,866
This is an emergency!

117
00:07:30,032 --> 00:07:31,367
Gosh.

118
00:07:31,909 --> 00:07:33,661
HUBBY

119
00:07:33,744 --> 00:07:35,329
DON'T ANSWER

120
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,460
Why won't you answer it?

121
00:07:42,795 --> 00:07:43,921
Isn't it your wife?

122
00:07:52,722 --> 00:07:55,641
Hey, why are you wearing
your sunglasses indoors?

123
00:07:56,726 --> 00:08:00,480
If you're embarrassed that people
might recognize you, just take it off.

124
00:08:00,730 --> 00:08:03,191
They'll stare even more,
thinking you're a lunatic.

125
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:14,076
Gosh, I don't know if this is clean.

126
00:08:18,873 --> 00:08:20,500
What is this? What the...

127
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:22,376
It's a cockroach!
What the hell?

128
00:08:29,175 --> 00:08:32,011
Can't you differentiate
between a cockroach and a fruit fly?

129
00:08:32,261 --> 00:08:33,930
It's gone now, dig in.

130
00:08:34,263 --> 00:08:35,973
What? Hey.

131
00:08:36,182 --> 00:08:39,477
Did you just dip your spoon you used
into my soup?

132
00:08:40,061 --> 00:08:42,063
What kind of savage are you?

133
00:08:42,146 --> 00:08:43,189
I'm so grossed out.

134
00:08:43,272 --> 00:08:46,317
You know what? Just take it all.
My gosh.

135
00:08:47,568 --> 00:08:49,570
It's been 30 years since we met,

136
00:08:50,071 --> 00:08:52,615
and you just had to pick a restaurant
just like yourself.

137
00:08:52,698 --> 00:08:54,075
What's wrong with this place?

138
00:08:54,158 --> 00:08:58,079
Hey, this is a famous restaurant
that's been around for 80 years.

139
00:09:00,498 --> 00:09:02,333
My, it's delicious.

140
00:09:02,416 --> 00:09:05,920
By the way, why did you want to see me
out of the blue after 30 years?

141
00:09:06,170 --> 00:09:09,048
You didn't even talk to me
back in the old days.

142
00:09:09,549 --> 00:09:12,802
Hey, did you talk to me
so casually even back in the day?

143
00:09:12,885 --> 00:09:14,345
I'm two years older than you.

144
00:09:14,428 --> 00:09:17,515
Age doesn't really matter
once you start working.

145
00:09:18,683 --> 00:09:20,810
You and I started interning
at Geosung Hospital

146
00:09:21,477 --> 00:09:23,646
in the same year, you know.

147
00:09:23,729 --> 00:09:25,523
All because you graduated

148
00:09:25,606 --> 00:09:27,400
two years late due to your bad grades.

149
00:09:27,483 --> 00:09:29,652
Watch it, prick.

150
00:09:29,735 --> 00:09:31,696
So, why did you want to see me?

151
00:09:32,196 --> 00:09:34,240
Why would such a nobleman like you

152
00:09:34,615 --> 00:09:37,159
need to see this lowborn man?

153
00:09:40,079 --> 00:09:40,913
You see,

154
00:09:41,622 --> 00:09:45,626
I did a little research on everyone
around me.

155
00:09:46,836 --> 00:09:48,879
I thought
that you were the least fortunate.

156
00:09:48,963 --> 00:09:50,756
So seeing you would comfort me.

157
00:09:51,924 --> 00:09:52,758
What?

158
00:09:53,259 --> 00:09:54,927
It really is comforting.

159
00:09:55,177 --> 00:09:57,430
Even someone like you
is moving on with your life,

160
00:09:57,513 --> 00:09:59,181
so why can't I?

161
00:09:59,265 --> 00:10:01,392
You're giving me so much courage.

162
00:10:02,810 --> 00:10:04,395
When I go back,

163
00:10:04,478 --> 00:10:06,147
I'll work very hard.

164
00:10:08,858 --> 00:10:10,610
Hey, let's be honest.

165
00:10:10,693 --> 00:10:14,530
Isn't it rare to meet someone get struck
by multiple misfortunes as you did?

166
00:10:14,614 --> 00:10:17,366
You divorced your first wife,

167
00:10:17,450 --> 00:10:20,911
and your second wife died
after giving birth to your son.

168
00:10:20,995 --> 00:10:23,080
Then your only child also--

169
00:10:23,164 --> 00:10:23,998
Stop.

170
00:10:24,081 --> 00:10:25,541
If you don't want this soup,

171
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:29,295
go to a fancy restaurant that you like
and get yourself a steak or something.

172
00:10:30,004 --> 00:10:31,130
Gosh.

173
00:10:32,340 --> 00:10:34,800
Right. I heard from Sang-sik

174
00:10:35,217 --> 00:10:37,720
that your first wife
who had left you for another man

175
00:10:37,803 --> 00:10:39,847
came back with Alzheimer's.

176
00:10:40,306 --> 00:10:42,933
How could she have the audacity
to come back?

177
00:10:43,017 --> 00:10:44,477
Is she a salmon or what?

178
00:10:46,562 --> 00:10:49,482
Don't you dare talk about that woman,
you asshole!

179
00:10:50,733 --> 00:10:53,319
Gosh, there's no need to get angry.

180
00:10:53,402 --> 00:10:54,278
Goodness.

181
00:11:23,724 --> 00:11:25,059
Cha-young!

182
00:11:27,436 --> 00:11:28,771
Ji-yong.

183
00:11:35,152 --> 00:11:36,696
-Mom!
-Ji-hun.

184
00:11:58,426 --> 00:12:02,138
Sharala, you miss him too, right?

185
00:12:03,931 --> 00:12:05,433
I do too.

186
00:12:22,783 --> 00:12:23,659
Ye-sol.

187
00:12:24,952 --> 00:12:26,036
Dr. Lee!

188
00:12:27,538 --> 00:12:28,789
What brings you here?

189
00:12:28,873 --> 00:12:30,124
Are you here with your mom?

190
00:12:30,207 --> 00:12:32,543
No, I'm here to check in
on Ji-yong's turtle.

191
00:12:34,044 --> 00:12:35,755
Her name is Sharala.

192
00:12:35,838 --> 00:12:38,507
It's a turtle Ji-yong used to look after.

193
00:12:39,091 --> 00:12:41,177
He asked me to take care of her

194
00:12:41,260 --> 00:12:43,387
when he isn't around.

195
00:12:46,015 --> 00:12:46,891
Where's your mom?

196
00:12:50,352 --> 00:12:52,688
She suddenly collapsed.

197
00:12:53,355 --> 00:12:55,357
She's in the ICU at the moment.

198
00:12:55,941 --> 00:12:57,276
They inserted tubes

199
00:12:57,359 --> 00:12:59,820
into her nose and throat.

200
00:13:00,946 --> 00:13:03,282
