00:18:04,249 --> 00:18:05,167
Director Kwon,

267
00:18:05,709 --> 00:18:07,002
what are you doing here?

268
00:18:09,505 --> 00:18:11,131
Are you trying to poop?

269
00:18:14,676 --> 00:18:16,011
No, I'm taking a piss.

270
00:18:35,572 --> 00:18:38,826
We can smell the pancakes from the ward.
How can I resist them?

271
00:18:38,909 --> 00:18:39,743
What is it?

272
00:18:39,827 --> 00:18:41,829
A parcel. It's for you.

273
00:18:41,912 --> 00:18:43,413
I can eat one, right?

274
00:18:46,667 --> 00:18:49,378
My gosh. If I gain weight,
it's all your fault.

275
00:18:49,461 --> 00:18:51,171
SENDER: LEE JUN

276
00:18:51,255 --> 00:18:54,258
This really is all your fault, not mine.

277
00:18:57,386 --> 00:18:59,471
I remembered it!

278
00:18:59,555 --> 00:19:01,014
I remembered it.

279
00:19:07,604 --> 00:19:09,106
It's clam porridge,

280
00:19:09,273 --> 00:19:10,858
so it needs clams!

281
00:19:10,941 --> 00:19:13,777
I'm such an idiot. Goodness.

282
00:19:13,861 --> 00:19:15,779
Just like red bean buns need red beans.

283
00:19:15,863 --> 00:19:17,114
It's so obvious.

284
00:19:17,197 --> 00:19:20,117
What got to my head, Alzheimer's?

285
00:19:20,325 --> 00:19:22,369
Hold on, I actually have that.

286
00:19:23,662 --> 00:19:27,457
I even remembered that I have Alzheimer's.
I'm doing pretty well today.

287
00:19:37,968 --> 00:19:39,344
It's good.

288
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:42,514
Do you want a bite?

289
00:19:42,598 --> 00:19:43,432
Yes!

290
00:19:44,224 --> 00:19:46,143
-Say "Ah."
-"Ah."

291
00:19:49,396 --> 00:19:50,647
It's so good.

292
00:19:51,398 --> 00:19:53,108
Would you like to try it too?

293
00:19:53,192 --> 00:19:55,027
No, it's okay.
Don't mind me.

294
00:19:56,195 --> 00:19:59,865
If we add a spoonful of sesame oil,

295
00:20:00,782 --> 00:20:02,242
it'll be even more delicious.

296
00:20:02,326 --> 00:20:05,162
Hold on, I remember
we had some pressed yesterday.

297
00:20:05,245 --> 00:20:06,246
Wait.

298
00:20:08,290 --> 00:20:09,875
Where did it go?

299
00:20:09,958 --> 00:20:11,919
She's a lot to take, isn't she?

300
00:20:12,085 --> 00:20:14,004
-I'll take a few of these pancakes.
-Sure.

301
00:20:14,504 --> 00:20:17,216
Gosh, I'm going to blame you
if I gain weight.

302
00:20:21,470 --> 00:20:23,013
Ta-da.

303
00:20:56,838 --> 00:20:57,673
What do you want?

304
00:20:58,590 --> 00:21:00,133
Where are you, beloved sister?

305
00:21:00,634 --> 00:21:02,135
-Hurry!
-What is it now?

306
00:21:02,219 --> 00:21:03,303
I have to make dinner.

307
00:21:03,387 --> 00:21:05,639
That is not important right now.

308
00:21:05,722 --> 00:21:09,518
This might totally transform your evening.

309
00:21:09,601 --> 00:21:10,978
What are you talking about?

310
00:21:11,061 --> 00:21:13,355
Look. Just look!

311
00:21:14,815 --> 00:21:16,316
Another dream car of mine

312
00:21:16,817 --> 00:21:18,277
is here.

313
00:21:18,944 --> 00:21:22,072
It's beautiful, like decalcomania.

314
00:21:22,155 --> 00:21:23,156
What about it?

315
00:21:23,323 --> 00:21:25,158
It's even better than this one,

316
00:21:25,242 --> 00:21:27,828
because that one
is a newer model than this one.

317
00:21:28,453 --> 00:21:30,330
-So what?
-And on top of that,

318
00:21:30,414 --> 00:21:33,750
the owner of this baby knows nothing
about my embarrassing past.

319
00:21:33,834 --> 00:21:38,338
Not a single ill-fated encounter with me,
which means no biases against me.

320
00:21:41,717 --> 00:21:43,468
Let's change our target.

321
00:21:44,177 --> 00:21:45,178
What?

322
00:21:46,346 --> 00:21:47,848
I've done some thinking.

323
00:21:48,056 --> 00:21:49,808
Marrying your first love?

324
00:21:49,891 --> 00:21:52,060
Come on, you know that's weird.

325
00:21:52,144 --> 00:21:54,604
I know someone who married her first love.

326
00:21:54,688 --> 00:21:56,690
She has an injury
that needs 4 weeks to heal,

327
00:21:56,773 --> 00:21:59,318
and the guy has dislocated bones.

328
00:21:59,401 --> 00:22:02,696
Tae-hyun! If you're here
to spew such nonsense, just go--

329
00:22:02,779 --> 00:22:04,865
Yes, ma'am, I already washed my feet

330
00:22:04,948 --> 00:22:06,867
and got plenty of sleep.

331
00:22:07,659 --> 00:22:09,703
Please, my beloved sister.

332
00:22:09,786 --> 00:22:11,913
Cha-young, please!

333
00:22:11,997 --> 00:22:15,500
You said Kang has no interest in you
whatsoever!

334
00:22:17,252 --> 00:22:20,797
I actually happened to meet
the owner of that baby earlier,

335
00:22:20,881 --> 00:22:22,758
and I thought he was my twin brother.

336
00:22:23,633 --> 00:22:26,261
He's too sexy for his own good,
just like me.

337
00:22:26,345 --> 00:22:27,888
He's unnecessarily handsome,

338
00:22:27,971 --> 00:22:29,723
and he's...

339
00:22:40,317 --> 00:22:43,445
Which one will be my brother-in-law?

340
00:22:45,614 --> 00:22:48,408
Eeny, meeny, miny, moe
Catch a tiger by the toe

341
00:22:49,368 --> 00:22:52,954
If he hollers, let him go
Eeny, meeny, miny, moe

342
00:22:53,789 --> 00:22:54,790
Moe!

343
00:23:20,690 --> 00:23:22,067
From now on,

344
00:23:22,734 --> 00:23:26,655
We're going to get rid of
that useless hospice and replace it

345
00:23:27,155 --> 00:23:31,159
with the best exclusive retirement
community in this country.

346
00:23:32,411 --> 00:23:35,122
Of course, we need
doctors that save lives.

347
00:23:36,581 --> 00:23:40,043
But I think there should also be doctors

348
00:23:40,127 --> 00:23:43,422
who can accompany patients
and help them to end their lives in peace,

349
00:23:43,880 --> 00:23:47,759
even when they are unable
to continue their treatment.

350
00:24:05,610 --> 00:24:08,280
Thank you for coming with me

351
00:24:08,864 --> 00:24:10,115
to pick raspberries.

352
00:24:13,326 --> 00:24:15,620
Thanks to you saving that doctor's wife,

353
00:24:15,704 --> 00:24:18,039
the public has become
much more friendly towards us.

354
00:24:19,666 --> 00:24:21,168
When we were here,

355
00:24:22,043 --> 00:24:23,336
it was nice.

356
00:24:23,962 --> 00:24:26,882
She's not that good at other things,
so she'll just open clams.

357
00:24:27,174 --> 00:24:30,177
She wants to thank the people here
for making Ji-yong happy.

358
00:25:18,558 --> 00:25:19,476
Excuse me.

359
00:25:28,485 --> 00:25:29,694
I want to avoid her.

360
00:25:31,363 --> 00:25:33,865
But she makes me feel worried.

361
00:25:34,491 --> 00:25:36,117
And I can't get her out of my head.

362
00:26:15,156 --> 00:26:17,158
Oh, Dr. Lee Jun?

363
00:26:20,704 --> 00:26:22,706
He's doing community service
in our hospital

364
00:26:22,789 --> 00:26:24,833
for assaulting Professor Jung.

365
00:26:25,375 --> 00:26:27,544
Was it 120 hours or 200 hours?

366
00:26:28,878 --> 00:26:30,714
If Dr. Lee didn't beat him up,

367
00:26:30,797 --> 00:26:32,340
I would've killed him.

368
00:26:36,386 --> 00:26:37,220
That's it, I quit.

369
00:26:39,055 --> 00:26:41,016
Mr. Im Seok-jo from Room 207 wants to play

370
00:26:41,891 --> 00:26:43,018
basketball with me,

371
00:26:43,101 --> 00:26:45,103
but I'm not feeling very well these days.

372
00:26:45,729 --> 00:26:47,314
Hey, you should do it.

373
00:26:49,190 --> 00:26:50,191
You know him, right?

374
00:26:50,275 --> 00:26:52,652
He used to play
in the national basketball team.

375
00:26:53,445 --> 00:26:55,238
Do your best.
The winner gets ramen.

376
00:26:58,074 --> 00:26:59,117
Good luck.

377
00:27:01,202 --> 00:27:02,203
Good luck.

378
00:27:06,458 --> 00:27:08,960
Gosh. Oh dear.

379
00:27:41,076 --> 00:27:42,160
You should go stop him.

380
00:27:42,243 --> 00:27:44,746
At this rate,
there won't be anything left.

381
00:27:56,424 --> 00:27:59,094
You're not supposed
to cut them in half like that.

382
00:28:01,346 --> 00:28:05,266
You should pick off
the anchovy's head like this first.

383
00:28:05,433 --> 00:28:08,061
Then, you split the belly open

384
00:28:08,186 --> 00:28:11,106
and pull its guts out.

385
00:28:12,399 --> 00:28:13,525
One more time?

386
00:28:14,067 --> 00:28:15,485
Pick off the head first,

387
00:28:16,444 --> 00:28:17,904
split the belly open,

388
00:28:19,030 --> 00:28:20,407
and pull out its guts.

389
00:28:20,949 --> 00:28:21,950
You should try.

390
00:28:28,665 --> 00:28:31,418
Good. That's how you do it.

391
00:28:33,670 --> 00:28:36,047
I'll do these again.

392
00:28:39,926 --> 00:28:42,053
And about the plate
that you sent us,

393
00:28:43,138 --> 00:28:45,515
I wanted to thank you for that.

394
00:28:46,266 --> 00:28:48,226
It's good to see you like this...

395
00:28:49,978 --> 00:28:52,856
I'm not supposed to say this, am I?

396
00:28:53,773 --> 00:28:56,526
It's better than criticizing
or sympathizing with me though.

397
00:28:57,861 --> 00:28:58,820
Good to see you too.

398
00:29:02,365 --> 00:29:04,200
I didn't mean to criticize you.

399
00:29:05,660 --> 00:29:07,245
So you sympathize with me.

400
00:29:08,288 --> 00:29:11,750
I did feel bad for you.

401
00:29:13,752 --> 00:29:15,044
I mean, about the situation.

402
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:19,007
Anyway, it doesn't mean
you don't sympathize with me.

403
00:29:22,135 --> 00:29:26,055
I'm telling you this as someone
who has lived as an object of pity.

404
00:29:26,139 --> 00:29:28,516
I don't think sympathy isn't all bad.

405
00:29:28,600 --> 00:29:30,643
It means you mean something, at least,

406
00:29:30,727 --> 00:29:32,896
to the person who sympathizes with you.

407
00:29:40,612 --> 00:29:42,489
-Hello.
-Hi.

408
00:29:47,410 --> 00:29:49,370
Are you done preparing the anchovies?

409
00:29:50,163 --> 00:29:52,040
As you can see, I'm still working on it.

410
00:29:53,416 --> 00:29:57,045
I just got a call
from Geosung Hospital in Seoul.

411
00:29:57,128 --> 00:30:00,507
-They asked me to take good care of you.
-I have nothing to do with it.

412
00:30:01,424 --> 00:30:02,675
I know.

413
00:30:02,759 --> 00:30:04,886
I guess it was an order from higher up

414
00:30:04,969 --> 00:30:08,014
or someone trying to show
excessive loyalty to you.

415
00:30:08,973 --> 00:30:10,308
Of all places,

416
00:30:10,391 --> 00:30:13,478
you came to our hospital
for your community service.

417
00:30:13,770 --> 00:30:17,941
So I assumed that you have
some good connections.

418
00:30:19,067 --> 00:30:20,485
I suppose that's an innuendo.

419
00:30:20,568 --> 00:30:23,780
Well, I didn't mean it that way.

420
00:30:24,697 --> 00:30:26,074
What I mean is

421
00:30:26,366 --> 00:30:28,868
that such things won't work for me,

422
00:30:28,952 --> 00:30:33,206
and that everything will be carried out
fairly and according to principle.

423
00:30:34,249 --> 00:30:36,835
-Also--
-I know what you mean.

424
00:30:37,001 --> 00:30:38,253
That's enough.

425
00:30:38,628 --> 00:30:41,297
I was going to tell you
that your work is over for the day.

426
00:30:43,174 --> 00:30:44,509
Don't forget to punch out.

427
00:30:44,592 --> 00:30:47,679
Tomorrow morning, you will wash
bedclothes and gowns just like today

428
00:30:47,762 --> 00:30:49,681
and work in the kitchen in the afternoon--

429
00:30:54,769 --> 00:30:55,979
He's a handful.

430
00:30:56,062 --> 00:30:56,896
Bye.

431
00:31:27,010 --> 00:31:28,511
Is everything going well?

432
00:31:30,430 --> 00:31:32,223
To get rid of this hospice.

433
00:31:36,686 --> 00:31:38,563
I heard Grandma made a promise to you.

434
00:31:38,855 --> 00:31:40,273
If you shut this hospice down,

435
00:31:41,149 --> 00:31:42,650
she will leave Geosung to you.

436
00:31:43,401 --> 00:31:45,278
I know. That's what she said.

437
00:31:52,368 --> 00:31:54,120
Do people in this hospital know that?

438
00:31:54,829 --> 00:31:56,831
That you're hatching a wicked plot

439
00:31:57,999 --> 00:31:59,918
with an innocent face like that.

440
00:32:05,131 --> 00:32:06,132
How would they know?

441
00:32:06,633 --> 00:32:08,217
It's a wicked plot like you said.

442
00:32:09,302 --> 00:32:10,803
People shouldn't know.

443
00:32:16,184 --> 00:32:17,310
What if I stop you?

444
00:32:19,771 --> 00:32:21,272
Go ahead and stop me if you can.

445
00:33:26,587 --> 00:33:27,797
Did I just hear thunder?

446
00:33:30,341 --> 00:33:32,593
I heard there would be a shower
in the evening.

447
00:33:47,692 --> 00:33:48,735
Come here.

448
00:34:00,455 --> 00:34:03,541
Right, so just live with your stupid dog
as if you're dead.

449
00:34:03,624 --> 00:34:05,043
Why must you get on my nerves?

450
00:34:18,848 --> 00:34:20,892
Dad, leave Kang alone from now on.

451
00:34:21,559 --> 00:34:24,270
You didn't have to send him to Libya
like the biggest coward

452
00:34:24,353 --> 00:34:26,355
because I could've totally beaten him.

453
00:34:26,731 --> 00:34:29,984
I could've crushed him with my skills.

454
00:35:05,144 --> 00:35:06,187
Stop it!

455
00:35:13,277 --> 00:35:14,946
What the hell are you doing?

456
00:35:35,633 --> 00:35:36,717
Let her apply it.

457
00:35:38,219 --> 00:35:40,429
You're a doctor.
Why are you being so stubborn?

458
00:35:40,972 --> 00:35:42,348
You want scars, is that it?

459
00:35:52,900 --> 00:35:53,818
Stay still.

460
00:35:55,194 --> 00:35:57,488
This would take about six weeks
to heal completely.

461
00:35:58,698 --> 00:36:01,951
Your jaw is all red.
You got a blow here, didn't you?

462
00:36:02,368 --> 00:36:05,037
I guess Dr. Lee Kang has a heavy punch.

463
00:36:06,414 --> 00:36:07,874
I'm stronger than him.

464
00:36:08,958 --> 00:36:10,501
He got beaten up worse than me.

465
00:36:10,585 --> 00:36:13,045
You must be proud.

466
00:36:13,129 --> 00:36:15,756
Here you are, doing community service
for assaulting a man,

467
00:36:15,840 --> 00:36:17,925
and having yet another fistfight
with a doctor.

468
00:36:18,342 --> 00:36:20,344
Do you want an award or something?

469
00:36:34,483 --> 00:36:35,985
What aren't you taking a shower?

470
00:36:36,068 --> 00:36:37,403
You'll catch a cold.

471
00:36:41,324 --> 00:36:44,660
Are you a teenager or what?
Is it a stormy period of puberty?

472
00:36:45,369 --> 00:36:47,455
You weren't like this
even when you were a kid.

473
00:36:48,539 --> 00:36:49,957
We fought like this as a kid.

474
00:36:50,791 --> 00:36:52,877
So? Do you want to fight him again?

475
00:36:55,213 --> 00:36:56,047
Yes.

476
00:36:56,756 --> 00:36:57,590
"Yes"?

477
00:36:58,799 --> 00:37:00,092
That's just our fate.

478
00:37:01,385 --> 00:37:04,430
We need to fight until either of us wins.

479
00:37:06,515 --> 00:37:07,683
For what?

480
00:37:08,517 --> 00:37:10,686
The winner gets Geosung?

481
00:37:13,773 --> 00:37:14,649
Fine.

482
00:37:14,941 --> 00:37:17,401
If that's your goal in life,
you should fight him.

483
00:37:17,485 --> 00:37:19,111
Fight him to death.

484
00:37:19,695 --> 00:37:20,863
I hope you win

485
00:37:20,947 --> 00:37:24,283
and take that Geosung bullcrap
with you when you die.

486
00:37:24,367 --> 00:37:26,994
It will be very heavy,
but make sure to bring it with you.

487
00:37:38,339 --> 00:37:40,007
Those who passed away here

488
00:37:41,259 --> 00:37:43,636
have taught you those lessons
with their whole lives.

489
00:37:45,638 --> 00:37:47,139
But is this what you've learned?

490
00:38:26,304 --> 00:38:27,847
Please take me to the parking lot.

491
00:38:30,433 --> 00:38:31,976
I thought you went home.

492
00:38:33,519 --> 00:38:34,770
Let me hold the umbrella.

493
00:38:35,563 --> 00:38:36,397
Let's go.

494
00:38:39,150 --> 00:38:40,735
This is a small umbrella.

495
00:38:54,290 --> 00:38:55,458
Where's your car?

496
00:38:56,292 --> 00:38:59,295
I don't have a car. I ride my bike.

497
00:38:59,378 --> 00:39:01,547
Since it's raining, I'll take the bus.

498
00:39:02,131 --> 00:39:03,215
I'll drive you then.

499
00:39:03,299 --> 00:39:04,925
It's okay.

500
00:39:05,259 --> 00:39:06,802
I can still take the last bus.

501
00:39:07,345 --> 00:39:08,971
Save your bus fare.

502
00:39:09,305 --> 00:39:10,931
It's for saving me from the rain.

503
00:39:13,017 --> 00:39:14,060
Let's go.

504
00:39:32,953 --> 00:39:34,121
It stopped raining.

505
00:39:36,248 --> 00:39:38,918
I'm still going to drive you home,
so just stay in the car.

506
00:39:39,877 --> 00:39:41,295
It's late anyway.

507
00:39:42,046 --> 00:39:43,422
And there might not be a bus.

508
00:39:45,257 --> 00:39:46,175
Then I guess

509
00:39:46,842 --> 00:39:48,844
I'll just make myself comfortable.

510
00:39:50,179 --> 00:39:51,222
Thank you.

511
00:40:08,114 --> 00:40:09,240
What's the matter?

512
00:40:09,740 --> 00:40:11,325
Did we do something wrong?

513
00:40:11,867 --> 00:40:14,036
I'm not sure. I wonder what we did wrong.

514
00:40:15,037 --> 00:40:15,955
Maybe he's jealous.

515
00:40:16,789 --> 00:40:19,041
-What?
-No, it's nothing.

516
00:40:22,962 --> 00:40:24,797
That driver must be in a hurry.

517
00:40:25,172 --> 00:40:26,841
I think he wants us to switch lanes.

518
00:40:27,216 --> 00:40:28,259
I don't care.

519
00:40:28,592 --> 00:40:29,760
I'm not budging.

520
00:40:48,446 --> 00:40:49,864
Did you hurt your wrist?

521
00:40:51,407 --> 00:40:53,159
I hurt it while I was beating Kang up.

522
00:40:53,826 --> 00:40:54,660
What?

523
00:40:59,707 --> 00:41:01,500
I got beaten up too, you know.

524
00:41:02,126 --> 00:41:03,544
Here and here.

525
00:41:04,420 --> 00:41:06,046
Here and here.

526
00:41:31,614 --> 00:41:32,990
Why did you guys fight?

527
00:41:33,949 --> 00:41:36,202
If I were you, I'd be extremely grateful.

528
00:41:36,285 --> 00:41:38,037
If it weren't for him, Ms. Kim--

529
00:41:38,454 --> 00:41:39,788
Let's not talk about that.

530
00:41:52,218 --> 00:41:53,552
INCOMING CALL

531
00:41:58,015 --> 00:41:58,849
Hello?

532
00:42:02,311 --> 00:42:03,437
Dr. Lee.

533
00:42:04,730 --> 00:42:06,148
I'm Ye-sol's father.

534
00:42:11,153 --> 00:42:13,405
Dr. Lee Kang saved Ms. Kim Hui-ju.

535
00:42:21,705 --> 00:42:23,249
I told you not to talk about that.

536
00:42:24,041 --> 00:42:25,084
Ms. Moon.

537
00:42:26,502 --> 00:42:27,962
You don't even know Kang well.

538
00:42:28,045 --> 00:42:30,339
-You don't know how evil he is.
-I do know him.

539
00:42:31,632 --> 00:42:32,466
You do?

540
00:42:33,092 --> 00:42:33,926
Yes, I do.

541
00:42:34,093 --> 00:42:37,596
I know that he isn't someone
you can criticize, badmouth,

542
00:42:37,680 --> 00:42:39,723
and judge however you want.

543
00:42:40,558 --> 00:42:41,934
Listen to me, Ms. Moon.

544
00:42:42,434 --> 00:42:45,229
Thank you for the ride.
I'll walk from here.

545
00:43:00,494 --> 00:43:02,204
I'm sorry.

546
00:43:03,872 --> 00:43:07,960
I was stupid and thoughtless.

547
00:43:10,129 --> 00:43:12,840
She wanted to stay at the hospice.

548
00:43:13,882 --> 00:43:17,052
But I forced her to leave.

549
00:43:17,136 --> 00:43:19,555
I have no authority over this.

550
00:43:20,222 --> 00:43:21,640
Please talk to the director.

551
00:44:05,517 --> 00:44:06,602
My goodness.

552
00:44:10,397 --> 00:44:11,231
It's a good thing.

553
00:44:19,448 --> 00:44:22,284
I'm sorry, Seong-cheol.

554
00:44:24,119 --> 00:44:26,914
I know I couldn't have afforded
to raise the both of you,

555
00:44:26,997 --> 00:44:29,583
but I never should've let you go.

556
00:44:31,126 --> 00:44:35,005
Did the Americans starve you
and mistreat you

557
00:44:36,006 --> 00:44:38,926
because you spoke a different language
and looked different?

558
00:44:39,009 --> 00:44:43,305
Is that why you got this horrible illness?

559
00:44:44,139 --> 00:44:45,391
I was happy.

560
00:44:46,433 --> 00:44:47,643
I was happy.

561
00:44:48,477 --> 00:44:50,354
My mom and dad

562
00:44:52,439 --> 00:44:54,400
-both loved me.
-Okay, okay.

563
00:44:54,900 --> 00:44:57,069
Okay, I understand.

564
00:44:58,904 --> 00:45:02,199
It's a relief that you met
rich parents, at least.

565
00:45:02,783 --> 00:45:05,577
My mom and I don't even have
a place of our own.

566
00:45:10,874 --> 00:45:12,084
My goodness.

567
00:45:13,502 --> 00:45:15,170
-Mom.
-Yes?

568
00:45:15,921 --> 00:45:17,214
I really wanted

569
00:45:18,632 --> 00:45:19,717
to meet you.

570
00:45:21,260 --> 00:45:22,261
Thankfully...

571
00:45:23,512 --> 00:45:24,555
Yes, what is it?

572
00:45:28,642 --> 00:45:30,352
I missed you.

573
00:45:32,062 --> 00:45:34,106
Yes, of course.

574
00:45:34,189 --> 00:45:36,316
Yes, I get what you mean. I understand.

575
00:45:38,110 --> 00:45:41,447
My goodness, what are we going to do?

576
00:45:41,947 --> 00:45:43,824
My goodness.

577
00:46:18,734 --> 00:46:20,944
So that's what Michael wanted to eat.

578
00:46:21,445 --> 00:46:25,574
The pork must've been added to the sauce
when the kimchi was initially made.

579
00:46:26,617 --> 00:46:28,911
We normally add pork separately.

580
00:46:28,994 --> 00:46:31,121
That's why her kimchi stew
tastes so different.

581
00:47:23,382 --> 00:47:24,550
What is she saying?

582
00:47:24,633 --> 00:47:28,262
I can't speak English. Speak Korean, okay?

583
00:47:28,846 --> 00:47:31,098
She says she wishes to try some.

584
00:47:35,561 --> 00:47:36,395
Here.

585
00:47:36,812 --> 00:47:39,314
I bet it tastes a thousand times better
than your food.

586
00:47:39,398 --> 00:47:43,569
My goodness, what in the world
did you feed my son?

587
00:47:43,652 --> 00:47:45,153
My gosh.

588
00:48:31,199 --> 00:48:34,494
I make the best kimchi stew in Korea.

589
00:48:37,915 --> 00:48:38,999
Try some.

590
00:48:39,291 --> 00:48:41,335
It's the kimchi stew
that you've been craving.

591
00:48:48,675 --> 00:48:51,595
It'd be great if Seong-cheol and I
could enjoy this kimchi stew

592
00:48:53,221 --> 00:48:54,222
along with some soju.

593
00:48:55,057 --> 00:48:57,184
You know what?
Let me go get a bottle of soju.

594
00:48:57,893 --> 00:48:59,770
He can't drink.

595
00:49:00,187 --> 00:49:01,271
I know that.

596
00:49:01,521 --> 00:49:04,358
I'm just joking around
because I'm really glad

597
00:49:04,775 --> 00:49:06,068
to see my brother again.

598
00:49:23,710 --> 00:49:26,338
How does it taste? It's good, isn't it?

599
00:49:26,755 --> 00:49:28,548
It tastes exactly the same, right?

600
00:49:30,884 --> 00:49:31,927
Yes, it's good.

601
00:49:32,594 --> 00:49:33,845
Nice.

602
00:49:34,262 --> 00:49:35,931
Your wish finally came true.

603
00:49:36,139 --> 00:49:37,557
How are you going to repay her?

604
00:49:38,558 --> 00:49:40,268
Stop talking nonsense.

605
00:49:41,144 --> 00:49:42,062
Want some rice?

606
00:49:42,145 --> 00:49:44,272
My baby Seong-cheol used to love it

607
00:49:44,356 --> 00:49:46,775
when I mixed his rice with my kimchi stew.

608
00:49:48,151 --> 00:49:49,152
No, it's okay.

609
00:49:49,778 --> 00:49:51,238
Have some more.

610
00:50:18,432 --> 00:50:21,351
Two regular-sized double cheese
cheesesteak sandwiches, please.

611
00:50:21,810 --> 00:50:23,061
With what kind of bread?

612
00:50:23,145 --> 00:50:26,064
-White bread for me.
-Wheat bread for me.

613
00:50:37,200 --> 00:50:38,201
Dr. Lee.

614
00:50:38,994 --> 00:50:40,746
Are you also here to eat a sandwich?

615
00:50:42,247 --> 00:50:44,166
We agreed to meet here today.

616
00:50:44,958 --> 00:50:46,209
That was yesterday.

617
00:50:46,543 --> 00:50:48,962
I told Cha-young
that I got stood up by you yesterday,

618
00:50:49,046 --> 00:50:51,673
and that's why she came here
to buy me a sandwich instead.

619
00:50:52,549 --> 00:50:54,217
It was yesterday, not today?

620
00:50:56,553 --> 00:50:58,555
LUNCH WITH MIN-YONG, 16TH

621
00:50:59,556 --> 00:51:00,557
You're right.

622
00:51:01,058 --> 00:51:03,185
I'm sorry. I got confused
because I was so busy.

623
00:51:04,144 --> 00:51:06,897
You should join us since you're here.

624
00:51:08,106 --> 00:51:09,691
She's right. You should join us.

625
00:51:22,454 --> 00:51:24,414
How is that going to make them clean?

626
00:51:24,623 --> 00:51:26,041
Put some effort into it.

627
00:51:31,421 --> 00:51:32,255
Gosh.

628
00:51:34,591 --> 00:51:37,177
I'm sorry. The washer just happened
to malfunction today.

629
00:51:37,677 --> 00:51:39,763
Are you sure
you didn't break it on purpose?

630
00:51:40,347 --> 00:51:42,307
My goodness, that's nonsense.

631
00:51:42,891 --> 00:51:44,226
We have nothing against you.

632
00:51:45,644 --> 00:51:48,146
The repairman is planning to come tonight.

633
00:51:48,772 --> 00:51:51,108
So the washer will work again tomorrow.

634
00:51:51,191 --> 00:51:52,818
I got a call. I should get going.

635
00:51:53,318 --> 00:51:54,820
I'm going to come back to check.

636
00:52:04,830 --> 00:52:05,705
What do you want?

637
00:52:14,047 --> 00:52:15,465
I'll wash the blankets.

638
00:52:15,549 --> 00:52:18,301
You, my man, can sit here and relax.

639
00:52:18,718 --> 00:52:19,761
Fortunately,

640
00:52:20,971 --> 00:52:22,556
there are no CCTVs here.

641
00:52:24,099 --> 00:52:25,100
Who are you?

642
00:52:25,642 --> 00:52:29,938
From now on, I'll help you clean,
do the laundry, and bathe the patients.

643
00:52:30,147 --> 00:52:31,857
I'll do all your work for you

644
00:52:31,940 --> 00:52:34,484
in the blind spots
where there are no CCTVs.

645
00:52:34,568 --> 00:52:37,195
You just need to make sure
you punch the clocks on time--

646
00:52:37,279 --> 00:52:38,780
I asked you who you are!

647
00:52:38,864 --> 00:52:40,991
I'm Tae-hyun. Moon Tae-hyun.

648
00:52:43,201 --> 00:52:45,203
You see, my sister works here

649
00:52:45,328 --> 00:52:47,414
as the chef in the cafeteria.

650
00:52:47,497 --> 00:52:50,625
She thinks it's nonsense that you're here
doing these kinds of stuff.

651
00:52:50,709 --> 00:52:52,460
So she told me

652
00:52:52,544 --> 00:52:54,754
that I should come and help you out.

653
00:52:56,047 --> 00:52:58,466
-I don't need your help. Get lost.
-If you want me to,

654
00:52:59,301 --> 00:53:00,385
I'll get lost.

655
00:53:02,596 --> 00:53:03,930
If you ever need my help,

656
00:53:04,347 --> 00:53:06,349
please give me a call.

657
00:53:15,734 --> 00:53:16,776
Crazy bastard.

658
00:53:25,160 --> 00:53:26,161
Hey.

659
00:53:27,162 --> 00:53:29,956
You're awfully rude to a stranger.
You don't even know me.

660
00:53:30,832 --> 00:53:32,542
I mean, now that I look at you,

661
00:53:32,626 --> 00:53:34,920
I can pretty much tell
what kind of person you are.

662
00:53:35,045 --> 00:53:40,050
Judging by your nasty
and mean personality,

663
00:53:40,425 --> 00:53:43,220
you'll obviously mistreat my sister
and look down on her.

664
00:53:43,803 --> 00:53:45,263
Gosh, it's making me get angry.

665
00:53:45,639 --> 00:53:48,183
I will never let that happen

666
00:53:48,266 --> 00:53:50,977
even if I have to ride buses
for the rest of my life.

667
00:53:51,353 --> 00:53:52,979
My gosh, this really pisses me off.

668
00:53:54,272 --> 00:53:56,191
I bet you're not even that rich.

669
00:53:56,691 --> 00:53:59,653
I mean, how am I supposed to know
if that car is really yours

670
00:53:59,819 --> 00:54:01,947
or if you just borrowed it
from someone else?

671
00:54:03,031 --> 00:54:04,866
My goodness.

672
00:54:04,950 --> 00:54:07,202
I know guys like you.

673
00:54:07,285 --> 00:54:09,829
You're here to do community service.

674
00:54:10,330 --> 00:54:15,585
And starting from head to toe,
you're wearing designer clothes.

675
00:54:16,169 --> 00:54:20,715
My gosh, I know that this is all fake.

676
00:54:21,007 --> 00:54:22,384
But I'll keep it a secret.

677
00:54:22,926 --> 00:54:25,470
So just make sure
you clean the blankets nice and clean.

678
00:54:26,012 --> 00:54:26,846
Sir.

679
00:54:26,930 --> 00:54:28,640
And don't forget

680
00:54:28,723 --> 00:54:31,309
to get rid of this stain right here.

681
00:54:32,227 --> 00:54:33,228
Sir.

682
00:54:34,479 --> 00:54:36,523
Also, people might slip and fall.

683
00:54:36,606 --> 00:54:38,024
So once you're done with this,

684
00:54:38,108 --> 00:54:41,444
make sure you wash the soap
off the ground.

685
00:54:41,528 --> 00:54:42,654
Sir.

686
00:54:45,657 --> 00:54:46,491
Hey.

687
00:54:47,075 --> 00:54:50,036
My gosh, he did it again.

688
00:54:50,829 --> 00:54:53,248
I can't believe this.

689
00:54:53,999 --> 00:54:57,252
Listen to me. My name isn't "Hey."

690
00:54:57,377 --> 00:55:00,005
I told you already
that my name is Moon Tae-hyun.

691
00:55:00,088 --> 00:55:01,715
I get that you're Moon Tae-hyun.

692
00:55:02,465 --> 00:55:03,883
Then what's your sister's name?

693
00:55:07,637 --> 00:55:08,972
Do I know her?

694
00:55:25,989 --> 00:55:27,490
You must've been very hungry.

695
00:55:28,700 --> 00:55:30,118
I'm talking about you both.

696
00:55:35,165 --> 00:55:38,001
By the way,
what happened to the Zika virus?

697
00:55:39,461 --> 00:55:40,754
Someone has the Zika virus?

698
00:55:42,756 --> 00:55:43,631
Dr. Lee.

699
00:55:44,924 --> 00:55:46,718
He had some symptoms
of Zika virus.

700
00:55:46,801 --> 00:55:49,179
Really? You shouldn't be here right now.

701
00:55:49,262 --> 00:55:52,223
You should get a checkup at a hospital
and get it treated.

702
00:55:52,307 --> 00:55:54,225
The Zika virus can't be treated.

703
00:56:02,984 --> 00:56:03,985
No.

704
00:56:04,944 --> 00:56:05,862
I...

705
00:56:06,237 --> 00:56:07,697
I don't have the Zika virus.

706
00:56:25,423 --> 00:56:28,718
I'm going to be late for school.
I'm leaving. Text me about the results!

707
00:56:29,469 --> 00:56:30,303
Hey!

708
00:56:33,723 --> 00:56:36,434
See? I'm 36.7°C.
My body temperature is normal.

709
00:56:38,186 --> 00:56:39,854
Are you sure this isn't broken?

710
00:56:41,773 --> 00:56:43,233
Here. Do I have a fever?

711
00:56:43,400 --> 00:56:44,776
Fever, rash, and red eyes.

712
00:56:44,859 --> 00:56:47,278
Do you notice any symptoms
of Zika virus infection?

713
00:57:09,926 --> 00:57:10,927
Get in.

714
00:57:15,473 --> 00:57:16,724
You didn't bring a bike.

715
00:57:17,016 --> 00:57:18,393
I can take the bus.

716
00:57:21,312 --> 00:57:23,857
You didn't seem to have any trouble
getting into...

717
00:57:24,315 --> 00:57:25,400
Dr. Lee Jun's car.

718
00:57:28,445 --> 00:57:29,779
Do you feel uneasy around me?

719
00:57:29,863 --> 00:57:31,781
Are you scared
that you might get infected?

720
00:57:35,535 --> 00:57:38,371
I'm sorry. I totally forgot.
I'll be right there.

721
00:57:42,375 --> 00:57:43,501
Let's go.

722
00:57:49,883 --> 00:57:53,761
I wasn't worried that I might get infected
with the Zika virus.

723
00:57:54,429 --> 00:57:57,056
I was worried
that you might really have it.

724
00:57:57,724 --> 00:57:59,184
You've got a lot on your hands.

725
00:58:01,352 --> 00:58:03,771
Come on, get in the car. Hurry.

726
00:58:22,123 --> 00:58:24,209
It's not like
I wanted him to give me a ride.

727
00:58:26,836 --> 00:58:29,547
It was raining that night,
and I was tired.

728
00:58:30,673 --> 00:58:32,467
And I honestly didn't want to walk

729
00:58:33,384 --> 00:58:34,677
all the way to the bus stop.

730
00:58:36,429 --> 00:58:40,683
But I wasn't really close enough
to ask him for a ride.

731
00:58:41,351 --> 00:58:45,563
I hesitated a really long time
before I actually got in his car.

732
00:58:49,609 --> 00:58:50,610
I'm just saying.

733
00:58:51,528 --> 00:58:52,737
Just giving you the facts.

734
00:59:29,148 --> 00:59:31,526
Thank you for the ride.

735
01:00:15,820 --> 01:00:17,864
It's not like
I wanted him to give me a ride.

736
01:00:18,448 --> 01:00:21,618
I hesitated a really long time
before I actually got in his car.

737
01:00:21,701 --> 01:00:24,829
I wasn't worried that I might get infected
with the Zika virus.

738
01:00:25,413 --> 01:00:28,041
I was worried
that you might really have it.

739
01:00:28,750 --> 01:00:30,168
You've got a lot on your hands.

740
01:00:31,127 --> 01:00:32,378
So you just stayed here

741
01:00:33,755 --> 01:00:35,048
and waited for me until now?

742
01:00:47,226 --> 01:00:48,686
I was worried about you.

743
01:01:32,689 --> 01:01:34,607
The people here at the hospice

744
01:01:35,733 --> 01:01:37,485
aren't just people who are dying.

745
01:01:37,568 --> 01:01:39,070
They're living their lives here.

746
01:01:40,071 --> 01:01:42,281
And they're cherishing
every day that they have.

747
01:01:43,241 --> 01:01:45,535
I know you like someone, Dr. Lee.

748
01:01:46,119 --> 01:01:47,537
Who do you think I like?

749
01:01:49,122 --> 01:01:50,206
HOSPITAL STAFF

750
01:01:50,707 --> 01:01:51,749
I don't like her.

751
01:01:51,958 --> 01:01:54,627
Then why are you blushing
and looking so flustered?

752
01:01:55,878 --> 01:01:59,215
What are you talking about?
I'm not blushing, and I'm not flustered.

753
01:02:02,260 --> 01:02:03,594
Do you like Kang?

754
01:02:05,722 --> 01:02:07,849
I don't have feelings for Dr. Lee Kang.

755
01:02:09,976 --> 01:02:12,395
He's a doctor I always thank
for having saved my life.

756
01:02:13,312 --> 01:02:16,399
But it's nothing more or less.

757
01:02:20,153 --> 01:02:22,447
Subtitle translation by Ja-won Lee

